WEDNESDAY EVENING A LOW 993 CENTRED IN THE N SEA DOMINATES CONDITIONS
ACROSS CULLERCOATS AND THE UK WITH HIGH PRESSURE 1033 CENTRED N OF THE
AZORES. THE LOW IN THE N SEA MOVS SLWY SWARDS THROUGH THURSDAY TOWARDS THE
LOW COUNTRIES FLN STEADILY AND LOSING ITS IDENTITY WITH A RIDGE OF HIGH
PRESSURE FLOWING INTO NERN UK UNDER THE INFLUENCE OF THE HIGH TO THE W. MEANWHILE
A QCKY DPN ATLANTIC LOW 980 BY MIDDAY THURSDAY MOVS E TO BE CENTRED SW
OF ICELAND. THIS LOW MOVS SLWY S AND E THROUGH FRIDAY AND SATURDAY CONTINUING
TO DEEPEN INITIALLY AND DRIVING AN ACTIVE FRONTAL ZONE ACROSS THE UK INTRODUCING
A STRG CYCLONIC FLOW. OCCASIONAL STRG WINDS ARE POSS THROUGH THURSDAY ACROSS
PARTS OF FISHER BEFORE EASING. BUT MORE WIDESPREAD STRG WINDS TO LOC GALES
SPREADING TO ALL AREAS FM THE NW THROUGH FRIDAY AND PERSISTING INTO SATURDAY
